One Important Caution

When comparing traditions at a very high level of abstraction, it’s easy to over-compress differences.

For example:
	•	In Buddhism, the goal is liberation from the cycle of rebirth.
	•	In Christianity, the resolution centers on redemption and relationship with God.
	•	In Hinduism, multiple metaphysical interpretations coexist.

Structurally they can look similar, but the philosophical details can be radically different.

So abstraction is powerful, but it also risks flattening nuance.

